# Cascade Knowledge Architecture
## Self-Reorganizing AI Systems Through Foundational Truth Propagation

**AI knowledge that reorganizes itself when paradigm shifts occur**

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Status: Experimental](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Experimental-orange.svg)]()

---

## What Is This?

Cascade Architecture is a **self-reorganizing knowledge system** where AI detects foundational-level information and automatically restructures its entire knowledge base from the ground up - like how quantum mechanics replaced classical physics and required rethinking everything built on top.

**The Core Insight:**
```
When new foundational truths emerge:
â”œâ”€â”€ Old foundations COMPRESS upward (become theories)
â”œâ”€â”€ New truth EXPANDS downward (becomes foundation)
â””â”€â”€ All dependent knowledge REORGANIZES (maintains coherence)
```

---

## The Problem It Solves

### Current AI Knowledge Systems:
- âŒ Trained once on data snapshot
- âŒ Can't reorganize when foundations proven wrong
- âŒ Accumulate contradictions as new info added
- âŒ Require complete retraining for paradigm shifts

### Real-World Consequences:
- **Medical AI:** Becomes outdated when treatment paradigms shift
- **Scientific AI:** Holds contradictory theories (classical + quantum as separate frameworks)
- **Financial AI:** Fails when market fundamentals change (2008 crisis, pandemic)
- **All AI:** Gets "stuck" on outdated foundations, can't self-correct

### Cascade Architecture Solution:
- âœ… Detects foundation-level information automatically
- âœ… Triggers reorganization when paradigm shifts
- âœ… Maintains coherence (no contradictions)
- âœ… Preserves valid knowledge (classical physics still works at macro scale)
- âœ… Self-corrects without retraining

---

## How It Works

### The Pyramid Structure
```
        â–² Edge Layer (Experimental Findings)
       â•±â”‚â•²  - Unvalidated hypotheses
      â•± â”‚ â•²  - Recent research
     â•±  â”‚  â•² - Bleeding edge
    â•±â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â•² - Expected to change
   â•±         â•²
  â•±â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â•² Theory Layer (Established Models)
 â•±             â•² - Peer-reviewed findings
â•±               â•² - Validated theories
â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ Foundation Layer (Core Axioms)
                    - Mathematical truths
                    - Physical laws
                    - Logical principles
```

**Knowledge organized by confidence level:**
- **Foundation:** Highest certainty, broadest explanatory power
- **Theory:** Mid certainty, domain-specific models
- **Edge:** Lowest certainty, experimental findings

---

### The Cascade Mechanism

**When new foundational truth detected:**
```
PHASE 1: DETECTION
â”œâ”€â”€ Calculate compression score (evidence Ã— explanatory power)
â”œâ”€â”€ Check for foundation conflicts
â””â”€â”€ If high compression + contradicts foundation â†’ TRIGGER CASCADE

PHASE 2: COMPRESSION
â””â”€â”€ Old foundations compress upward (become theories with limited validity domains)

PHASE 3: EXPANSION
â””â”€â”€ New truth expands downward (becomes new foundation)

PHASE 4: REORGANIZATION
â”œâ”€â”€ Trace all dependent knowledge
â”œâ”€â”€ Re-evaluate compatibility with new foundation
â”œâ”€â”€ KEEP: Compatible knowledge (update dependencies)
â”œâ”€â”€ DEMOTE: Uncertain knowledge (move to edge for revalidation)
â””â”€â”€ REMOVE: Incompatible knowledge (contradicted by new foundation)

PHASE 5: VALIDATION
â”œâ”€â”€ Calculate coherence (contradictions eliminated?)
â”œâ”€â”€ Test predictions (accuracy improved?)
â””â”€â”€ Verify structure (efficiency gained?)
```

